|WKO===========

|YKOPut something in or on something else, such as "put bottle in bag."

The second form allows you to put all of one specific item on or
in something else, such as
    put all sword in bag    OR
    put all swords in bag
    
|WKBSyntax: |YKBput <object> <preposition> <object>
        put all <object> <preposition> <object>

|WKBSee also: |YKBdrop, give, get
